---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
    title="Thank You | G2Labs"
    description="Thank you for reaching out to G2Labs. Your inquiry has been sent."
>
    <section class="page-intro panel">
        <p class="eyebrow">Thank you</p>
        <h1>Your message has been sent.</h1>
        <p class="lead">
            Thanks for reaching out. I will review your message and get back to
            you as soon as practical.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel panel-shell split-section">
        <div>
            <p class="eyebrow">What happens next</p>
            <h2>The next reply should be grounded in the actual problem you described.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-shell">
            <p>
                If your message included the product stage, platform, protocols,
                and the delivery bottleneck, that is usually enough to start a
                useful first conversation.
            </p>
            <p>
                In the meantime, you can review selected work, public products,
                or the contact page again if you want to send more context.
            </p>
            <div class="product-links">
                <a class="button button-primary" href="/work">See selected work</a>
                <a class="button button-secondary" href="/products">Open public products</a>
                <a class="button button-secondary" href="/contact">Back to contact</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>